In Julia, Write a function `find`. It computes median over arbitrary array. Provide an example

Here is the implementation of the `find` function in Julia:
```julia
function find(arr)
    return median(arr)
end
```
This function takes an array as input and returns its median value.

Here's an example usage of this function:
```julia
julia> arr = [1, 2, 3, 4, 5]
julia> find(arr)
3
```
This will return the median value of the array `arr`, which is 3 in this case.
